name: Howard County Health Department
tweet: Did you know? We provide PCR testing for COVID-19 using the FDA-authorized Azova saliva test kit. It's more comfortable than traditional nasal swab testing, and it's FREE. All the details:  https://t.co/mM9Lchr63F  A handy tutorial:  https://t.co/LuAg89GAc4

name: Howard County Health Department
tweet: It's been 40 years since the first 5 cases of what became known as AIDS were reported. On #WorldAIDSDay (12/1), we honor the 36 million we've lost worldwide. Join us in wearing red or black to memorialize how far we've come, and tag us in your pics to be featured here.  https://t.co/Yrcni6JI1i

name: Howard County Health Department
tweet: Don't miss these moments. This year's plays and musicals (and every bold soliloquy and booming high note!) brought to you by the COVID-19 vaccine. Get yours today:  https://t.co/J4js5EAuI6  https://t.co/xAHk8uXzqJ

name: Howard County Health Department
tweet: On 12/1, @afspmaryland and @hoconaacp will host "Talk Saves Lives." Join us to learn about the research on suicide prevention, what you can do to fight suicide, common risk factors and warning signs, and how to keep yourself and others safe:  https://t.co/kj1OydRT1z  https://t.co/RgYuB72WW2

name: Howard County Health Department
tweet: On #WorldAIDSDay2021 (that's Wednesday, 12/1) we'll offer FREE HIV testing from our HoCo Health RV! Come on by from 9:30AM-3:30PM. We'll be parked at 8930 Stanford Blvd. in Columbia.  https://t.co/1obLulCyJV

name: Howard County Health Department
tweet: If you smoke, you may worry about COVID-19 and smoking. Scientists are still learning, but we know that being a smoker increases your risk for severe illness and weakens the immune system, making it harder to fight disease. Ready to quit? Here's a start:  https://t.co/Q3fcZ9y14u

name: Howard County Health Department
tweet: Meet Katelyn. She's sharing her long COVID story so you won't have one. Getting vaccinated is the best protection against COVID-19 and long COVID. Find a clinic here in HoCo that's right for you at  https://t.co/J4js5ES5zE  https://t.co/8diK63YnYh

tweet: We're grateful for all of you, HoCo. Thank you for doing your part to make our beautiful county a healthier place. Sending warm holiday wishes to you and yours from all of us at HoCo Health.  https://t.co/grSA3aY4Ks

name: Howard County Health Department
tweet: Happy Thanksgiving, HoCo! Reminder: we will NOT hold testing or vaccine clinics on November 26th, December 24th, or December 31st in recognition of the winter holidays.

name: Howard County Health Department
tweet: As cases rise, you may want or need a COVID test. We're here for you. Every Mon, Wed, and Fri from 9:30AM-12:30PM, we offer FREE testing at 8930 Stanford Blvd. in Columbia. Rapid testing is also available 7 days a week. Full details here:  https://t.co/mM9Lch9uF5  https://t.co/X2HqMhglo5

name: Howard County Health Department
tweet: Keep foods separated. Cook food thoroughly. Do not eat raw food or batter. Thaw your turkey safely. And of course, wash your hands. Just in time for the holiday, the CDC has some pointers on preparing and eating food safely this season:  https://t.co/XFZEBmwtKV
